Title : Chicago Lakeshore Hospital
Text : {{external links|date=May 2019}}
{{news release|article|date=January 2017}}{{Cleanup rewrite|date=July 2019}}

'''Chicago Lakeshore Hospital''' is a private behavioral health and addiction treatment center located in the north side of the city of Chicago. 

In 2018, Federal authorities announced they were pulling funding from the hospital under investigation following numerous allegations of sexual abuse, assault and patient safety violations. All children in state care were removed from the facility after the ACLU of Illinois took actio. 

Federal authorities Terminated Lakeshoreâ€™s Medicare agreement Dec. 15. Several people familiar with the issue expect that Medicaid decertification will follow.

